**[1848, 04-07] Ms.B.1.6.2.70**

Estlin, John Bishop, to Samuel May, Jr. [Bristol]. Thinks a limited
monarchy would be best for France. Discusses Irish troubles. Says
Chartist disturbances are expected in London. {Bulk in {u}BAA{/u}.}

[Concerning the “Unitarian Reply”:] “What an excellent article that is
of Theo. Parker’s in the Lib. Bell, ‘Come & do it better.’” BAA: Praises
Lamartine but denounces Ledru Rollin. Criticizes Irish Repeal.


